[
  {
    "content_id": 797873,
    "reference_id": 17900,
    "title": "約珥書 1:1",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29001001",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<ul><li><p>耶和華的話提供了這個信息（字面意思是<em>耶和華的話來了</em>；和合本譯為：耶和華的話臨到）：耶和華並非人類先知，祂是這些話語的終極來源。</p></li><li><p>約珥這個名字的意思是「耶和華<span>（</span>雅巍）是神」。約珥的父親——毗土珥——只出現在這節經文中，除此之外我們對他一無所知。</p></li></ul>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29001001",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:1",
          "end_ref": "29001001",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:1"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797865,
    "reference_id": 17892,
    "title": "約珥書 1:1–2:17",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29001001-29002017",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>約珥描述了襲擊猶大和耶路撒冷的毀滅性蝗災。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29001001",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:1",
          "end_ref": "29002017",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 2:17"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797875,
    "reference_id": 17902,
    "title": "約珥書 1:2",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29001002",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<ul><li><p>當聽我的話：約珥召集這片土地上的居民密切留意這預言的話。</p></li><li><p>領袖們哪（字面意思是<em>長老</em>；和合本譯為：老年人哪）：先知詢問群體中的老年人，這樣的事以前發生過嗎？沒有——這場災難在神子民的歷史上是<span>獨一無二的</span>。</p></li></ul>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29001002",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:2",
          "end_ref": "29001002",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:2"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797876,
    "reference_id": 17903,
    "title": "約珥書 1:3",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29001003",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>神的子民要告訴未來的世代所發生的事，以便他們的後代能從他們的教訓中受益（參<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:9\">申4:9</a>，<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:20-Deut6:25\">6:20–25</a>）。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29001003",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:3",
          "end_ref": "29001003",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:3"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797877,
    "reference_id": 17904,
    "title": "約珥書 1:4",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29001004",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>降臨到猶大的災難是一場毀滅性的蝗災。一些註釋者認為，這裡提到的四種<em>蝗蟲</em>代表了征服以色列的四個古代帝國。另一些人則認為，這些詞彙是表示蝗蟲發展的四個階段。最有可能的是，先知使用多個用語來強調這一波又一波的貪婪昆蟲所造成之破壞的嚴重程度。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29001004",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:4",
          "end_ref": "29001004",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:4"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797878,
    "reference_id": 17905,
    "title": "約珥書 1:5",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29001005",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>要清醒哭泣：先知試圖喚醒人們，提醒他們蝗災的嚴重性。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29001005",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:5",
          "end_ref": "29001005",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:5"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797879,
    "reference_id": 17906,
    "title": "約珥書 1:7",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29001007",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>蝗蟲的破壞力在古代和現代都有充分的記載。這些貪婪的昆蟲會吞噬穀物和蔬菜等一年生作物，並摧毀多年生的果樹和藤蔓，<span>使樹枝變得光禿潔白</span>。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29001007",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:7",
          "end_ref": "29001007",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:7"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797880,
    "reference_id": 17907,
    "title": "約珥書 1:8",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29001008",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>像新娘（字面意思是<em>處女</em>）一樣哭泣（和合本譯為：當哀號，像處女）：猶大被比喻為一位已訂婚的年輕女子，因未婚夫去世而婚姻未得完滿。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29001008",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:8",
          "end_ref": "29001008",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:8"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797881,
    "reference_id": 17908,
    "title": "約珥書 1:9",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29001009",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>蝗災威脅著猶大百姓的生計，並使耶路撒冷聖殿每日的動物和穀物及酒的獻祭都斷絕了（參<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:38-Exod29:41\">出29:38–41</a>；<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:2-Num28:8\">民28:2–8</a>）。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29001009",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:9",
          "end_ref": "29001009",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:9"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797866,
    "reference_id": 17893,
    "title": "約珥書 1:10",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29001010",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>蝗蟲摧毀了古代以色列的三種主要作物：穀物、葡萄和橄欖油。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29001010",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:10",
          "end_ref": "29001010",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:10"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797867,
    "reference_id": 17894,
    "title": "約珥書 1:12",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29001012",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>乾旱加劇了蝗災的破壞性，一切都枯乾衰殘（另見<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:19-Joel1:20\">1:19–20</a>）。在靈性上，人們的喜樂也隨著果樹一起盡都消滅了。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29001012",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:12",
          "end_ref": "29001012",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:12"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797868,
    "reference_id": 17895,
    "title": "約珥書 1:13–14",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29001013-29001014",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>祭司應帶領所有人在聖殿舉行公開的哀悼儀式。他們外在的行為必須與內心真實的改變相符（見<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:13\">2:13</a>）。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29001013",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:13",
          "end_ref": "29001014",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:14"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797869,
    "reference_id": 17896,
    "title": "約珥書 1:15",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29001015",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<ul><li><p>蝗災並不僅只是一個自然事件，而是耶和華的日子臨近的徵兆。自公元前700年間阿摩司時代起（<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:18\">摩5:18</a>），先知們就曾預言在未來某個時刻，神將介入人類歷史，審判惡人並為義人伸冤。</p></li><li><p>毀滅從全能者來到：希伯來文本強調了<em>毀滅</em>（shod）和<em>全能者</em>（shadday）這兩個詞的諧音。</p></li></ul>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29001015",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:15",
          "end_ref": "29001015",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:15"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797870,
    "reference_id": 17897,
    "title": "約珥書 1:17",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29001017",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>蝗災和乾旱大大減少了糧食的供應，使得穀倉都空了。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29001017",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:17",
          "end_ref": "29001017",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:17"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797871,
    "reference_id": 17898,
    "title": "約珥書 1:18",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29001018",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>猶大地的居民因饑荒而受苦；即便綿羊山羊，這些能在極其貧乏的草場上生存的動物，現在也因缺乏食物而哀鳴。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29001018",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:18",
          "end_ref": "29001018",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:18"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797872,
    "reference_id": 17899,
    "title": "約珥書 1:19",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29001019",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>耶和華，幫助我們！（字面意思是<em>向你</em>，耶和華，<em>我呼求；</em>和合本譯為：耶和華啊，我向你求告）：約珥以懇切的禱告作為對這場災害的回應。人唯一的辦法就是轉向掌管天地的耶和華，呼求祂的良善；只有祂能扭轉他們絕望的局面。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29001019",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:19",
          "end_ref": "29001019",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:19"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797874,
    "reference_id": 17901,
    "title": "約珥書 1:20",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29001020",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>所有<span>受造之物</span>都因人類的罪而受苦（<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:17-Gen3:18\">創3:17–18</a>，<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:2\">9:2</a>；<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:20-Rom8:21\">羅8:20–21</a>）——甚至野生動物也向神呼求。翻譯為「呼求」的這個詞在希伯來文中與<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps42:1\">詩篇四十二篇1節</a>中描述鹿「切慕」溪水的那個詞相同。野獸為食物和水迫切呼求，這為猶大和耶路撒冷的百姓該如何尋求他們的神樹立了榜樣（參<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:3\">賽1:3</a>）。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29001020",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:20",
          "end_ref": "29001020",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 1:20"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797896,
    "reference_id": 17923,
    "title": "約珥書 2:1",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29002001",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>當一個古老的城遭到攻擊時，城牆上的守望者就會透過吹角——一種稱為羊角號的蘭角樂器（另見<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:15\">2:15</a>），來發出警報，召集所有防禦者擊退敵人。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29002001",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 2:1",
          "end_ref": "29002001",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 2:1"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797882,
    "reference_id": 17909,
    "title": "約珥書 2:1–11",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29002001-29002011",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>有些人認為這一部分是第二次記述第<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:1-Joel1:20\">一</a>章所描述的蝗災，但在第<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:1-Joel1:20\">一</a>章中，災害就已經過去了，並且這一部分中的動詞時態看起來是在描述一個未來事件。因此，其他人將其視為對另一場蝗災的警告。還有一些註釋者認為這一段描述的是末後神的日子臨到，用了蝗災的語言來描述入侵的人類軍隊。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29002001",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 2:1",
          "end_ref": "29002011",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 2:11"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797904,
    "reference_id": 17931,
    "title": "約珥書 2:2",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29002002",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>一些宗教領袖曾教導耶路撒冷和猶大的百姓，耶和華的日子將是神百姓蒙福的時刻。約珥與先知西番雅（<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph1:15\">番1:15</a>）相呼應，宣告那將是一個黑暗、幽冥的日子（另見<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:18-Amos5:20\">摩5:18–20</a>）。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29002002",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 2:2",
          "end_ref": "29002002",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 2:2"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797907,
    "reference_id": 17934,
    "title": "約珥書 2:3",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29002003",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>入侵的軍隊帶來的破壞將如同肆虐的野火。在受攻擊之前，這片土地看起來像伊甸園，在此之後，它將只剩荒涼（與<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:3\">賽51:3</a>和<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:35\">結36:35</a>的對比）。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29002003",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 2:3",
          "end_ref": "29002003",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 2:3"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797908,
    "reference_id": 17935,
    "title": "約珥書 2:4–5",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29002004-29002005",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<ul><li><p>牠們的形狀如馬：蝗蟲與馬之間的相似性（另見<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:7\">啟9:7</a>）強化了蝗蟲如軍隊的意象。</p></li><li><p>聆聽牠們發出的響聲（和合本譯為：在山頂蹦跳的響聲）：蝗蟲群發出的響聲可震耳欲聾。</p></li></ul>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29002004",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 2:4",
          "end_ref": "29002005",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 2:5"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797909,
    "reference_id": 17936,
    "title": "約珥書 2:6",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29002006",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>恐懼籠罩著所有人（和合本譯為：眾民傷慟）：對入侵的預期，<span>使百姓為</span><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:12-Joel2:14\">二章12至14節</a>中的悔改呼召做好準備。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29002006",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 2:6",
          "end_ref": "29002006",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 2:6"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797910,
    "reference_id": 17937,
    "title": "約珥書 2:7–9",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29002007-29002009",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>蝗蟲入侵城市及農業區域，像訓練有素的軍隊一樣前進，爬過城牆並在城市上空成群結隊。它們會找到每一個入口，甚至像小偷一樣從窗戶爬進去。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29002007",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 2:7",
          "end_ref": "29002009",
          "end_ref_usfm": "JOL 2:9"
        }
      ],
      "resource": []
    }
  },
  {
    "content_id": 797883,
    "reference_id": 17910,
    "title": "約珥書 2:10",
    "media_type": "Text",
    "index_reference": "29002010",
    "language": "zht",
    "content": "<p>天地震動是<em>神顯現</em>的典型徵兆，即神的顯現（見<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:16-Exod19:19\">出19:16–19</a>；<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:13\">賽13:13</a>；<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah1:5-Nah1:6\">鴻1:5–6</a>）。日月昏暗象徵著神聖的審判（<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:9-Isa13:11\">賽13:9–11</a>）。</p>",
    "associations": {
      "passage": [
        {
          "start_ref": "29002010",
          "start_ref_usfm": "JOL 2:10",
          "end_ref": "29002010",
